4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING PARTICIPATION IN THE FIREFIGHTERS' UNIFIED
5 RETIREMENT SYSTEM TO INCLUDE AIRPORT AUTHORITY PUBLIC SAFETY EMPLOYEES; REVISING
6 AND PROVIDING A DEFINITION; AMENDING SECTIONS 19-13-104 AND 19-13-210, MCA; AND
7 PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 19-13-104, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "19-13-104. Definitions. Unless the context requires otherwise, the following definitions apply in this
13 chapter:
14 (1) Any reference to "city" or "town" includes those jurisdictions that, before the effective date of a
15 county-municipal consolidation, were incorporated municipalities, subsequent districts created for urban
16 firefighting services, or the entire county included in the county-municipal consolidation.
17 (2) "Compensation" means:
18 (a) for a full-paid firefighter, the remuneration paid from funds controlled by an employer in
19 payment for the member's services before any pretax deductions allowed by state and federal law are made;
20 (b) for a part-paid firefighter employed by a city of the second class:
21 (i) 15% of the regular remuneration, excluding overtime, holiday payments, shift differential
22 payments, compensatory time payments, and payments in lieu of sick leave, paid on July 1 of each year to a
23 newly confirmed, full-paid firefighter of the city that employs the part-paid firefighter; or
24 (ii) if that city does not employ a full-paid firefighter, 15% of the average regular remuneration,
25 excluding overtime, holiday payments, shift differential payments, compensatory time payments, and payments
26 in lieu of sick leave, paid on July 1 of each year to all newly confirmed, full-paid firefighters employed by cities
27 of the second class.
28 (c) Compensation for full-paid and part-paid firefighters does not include:
